# Implementation Plan: BlogVerse Android Application

This plan outlines the steps to convert the existing React frontend into a native Android application using Capacitor. This allows for a single codebase to serve both web and mobile users while utilizing the existing FastAPI backend on Render.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Android Studio Requirement:** The user must have Android Studio installed on their local machine to perform the final compilation and APK generation.

> [!NOTE]
> **API URL:** The mobile app must be configured to use the production backend URL (`https://blogverse-api-ssvc.onrender.com/api`) instead of `localhost`.

